Step-by-Step Configuration
Step	Description
Device Placement	Router placed at top, two switches (2960) placed below, four PCs divided evenly between switches
Connections	All devices connected using copper straight-through cables; switch-to-router ports chosen carefully to leave room for expansion
VLAN Creation & Assignment	VLAN 10 named “dept A” on Switch 0; VLAN 20 named “dept B” on Switch 2; all FastEthernet ports assigned accordingly
Router Interface Configuration	Router GigabitEthernet0/0 configured with IP 192.168.10.1/24 for VLAN 10; GigabitEthernet0/1 with IP 192.168.20.1/24 for VLAN 20
PC IP Configuration	PCs assigned IPs in the respective VLAN subnets with default gateways matching router interfaces
